Usage: taup refltrans [--abs] [--debug] [--down] [--help] [--legend] [--pwave]
                      [--shwave] [--swave] [--up] [--verbose]
                      [--anglestep=<angleStep>] [--depth=<depth>]
                      [--mapwidth=<mapwidth>] [--mapwidthunit=<mapWidthUnit>]
                      [-o=<outFile>] [--prop=<toolPropsFilename>]
                      [--rpstep=<rayparamStep>] [-x=<xAxisType>] [--xminmax=x
                      x]... [--yminmax=y y]... [--layer=<layerParams>
                      <layerParams> <layerParams> <layerParams> <layerParams>
                      <layerParams>]... [-y=<yAxisType> [<yAxisType>
                      [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType>
                      [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType>
                      [<yAxisType>]]]]]]]]]]... [--text | --json | --gmt |
                      --svg] [[--mod=<modelname>] [-h=<sourceDepth>]
                      [--stadepth=depth] [--scat=s s]...]
plot reflection and transmission coefficients for a discontinuity
      --abs                absolute value of amplitude factor
      --anglestep=<angleStep>
                           step in degrees when x is degrees
      --debug              enable debugging output
      --depth=<depth>      Depth in model to get boundary parameters
      --down
      --help               display this help message
      --layer=<layerParams> <layerParams> <layerParams> <layerParams>
        <layerParams> <layerParams>

      --legend             create a legend
      --mapwidth=<mapwidth>
                           plot width in inches for GMT, pixels for SVG.
      --mapwidthunit=<mapWidthUnit>
                           plot width unit for GMT. Default is i for inchs
  -o, --output=<outFile>   output to file, default is stdout.
      --prop=<toolPropsFilename>
                           load defaults from properties file
      --pwave              incident P wave
      --rpstep=<rayparamStep>
                           step in ray param when x is ray param
      --shwave             incident SH wave
      --swave              incident S wave
      --up
      --verbose            enable verbose output
  -x=<xAxisType>           X axis data type, one of degree, rayparam, default
                             is degree
      --xminmax=x x        min and max x axis for plotting
  -y=<yAxisType> [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType>
       [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType> [<yAxisType>]]]]]]]]]
                           Y axis data type, one of Rpp, Rps, Rsp, Rss, Tpp,
                             Tps, Tsp, Tss, Rshsh, Tshsh, default is all
      --yminmax=y y        min and max y axis for plotting
Output Type
      --gmt                outputs as GMT
      --json               outputs as JSON
      --svg                outputs as SVG
      --text               outputs as text
Model Args
  -h, --sourcedepth=<sourceDepth>
                           source depth in km
      --mod, --model=<modelname>
                           use velocity model "modelname" for calculations
                                                 Default is iasp91.
      --scat, --scatter=s s
                           scattering depth and distance in degrees, which may
                             be negative. Only effects phases with 'o' or 'O'
                             in the phase name.
      --stadepth=depth     the receiver depth in km for stations not at the
                             surface
